		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You could always do it in two steps. First start by making a game in a high-level tool such as Construct, taking into account the NES's graphical limits. Then find someone to port it to the NES. That's how <em>STREEMERZ</em> was made. The point is to have a game made.

		

		</td>
